    feat(crud-feature): edit + delete endpoints and UI
    
    Backend (internal/api/server.go, dto.go):
    - PATCH /api/features/{id}: partial update of title and/or priority only.
      Reloads feature first, validates (empty_title/title_too_long/invalid_priority),
      rejects in_progress/waiting_for_feedback/gate_blocked with 409 feature_processing,
      preserves immutable fields (id/intake_path/spec_dir/current_phase/created_at),
      sets updated_at. FR-001..FR-004, FR-010, FR-011; CON-001..CON-004.
    - DELETE /api/features/{id}: hard delete via existing ON DELETE CASCADE schema.
      Rejects mid-processing with 409 feature_processing (IsProcessing + IsSessionAlive),
      rejects non-deletable statuses with 400 not_deletable, returns 204 on success,
      404 feature_not_found for unknown id. FR-005..FR-009; CON-005, CON-007, CON-012.
    - EditFeatureRequest DTO with pointer fields (omitted fields not zeroed).
    
    UI (api/client.ts, types/index.ts, FeatureDetail.tsx, FeatureCard.tsx):
    - editFeature + deleteFeature client functions; EditFeatureRequest type.
    - Detail page: Edit button -> inline edit form (title + priority, pre-filled,
      Save/Cancel), Delete button -> window.confirm dialog -> navigate to dashboard.
      Edit/Delete disabled with tooltips for non-editable/non-deletable statuses.
      Invalidates ['features'] and ['feature', id] caches; success toasts. FR-012..FR-019.
    - Dashboard FeatureCard: delete affordance (button) with confirm for
      deletable features, stops propagation so the card link isn't followed. US-003.

